name: Matthew Beck
body:
### My Projects
For my software engineering class, we were tasked with building a 'social network' of sorts, which can be found [here](https://github.com/beckmc/RocketRoad). It was collaboration project with @everlastingbugstopper and Kris Blau, where I was in charge of the back-end of the project.

In my data structures and algorithms class, I wrote a recipe book program in Java, which you can learn more about [here](https://github.com/beckmc/RecipeBook-CS150). After the course ended, I made an Objective-C version of it which implements a GUI and features some other changes, which can be found [here](https://github.com/beckmc/RecipeBook).
***
### My Courses
* CS 104 - Computer Gaming (Fall 2014)
* CS 150 - Data Structures & Algorithms (Spring 2015)
* CS 202 - Analysis of Algorithms (Fall 2015)
* CS 203 - Computer Organization (Fall 2015)
* CS 205 - Software Engineering (Spring 2016)
* CS 301 - Principles of Programming Languages (Spring 2016)
* CS 320 - Database Management Systems (Fall 2016)

***
### Other Stuff
Sometimes I write things about my other passion, politics, on Medium. You can find my profile at <https://medium.com/@mcbeckjr> and check out some of the things I have written there.

Want to see my resume? You can find it [here](https://github.com/beckmc/Resume/blob/master/Resume.pdf).
***
### Contact Me
You can get in touch with me at beckmc@lafayette.edu
